<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Probe on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/probe/</link><description>Recent content in Probe on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/probe/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] Docker Health Check Failed — health check failed</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/docker/healthcheck-failed/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/docker/healthcheck-failed/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="docker-health-check-failed--health-check-failed"&gt;Docker Health Check Failed — health check failed&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A health check fails when the command specified in the Dockerfile or compose file returns a non-zero exit code or times out. Docker marks the container as unhealthy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Application is not responding to health check requests&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Health check command is incorrect or has wrong path&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Application takes too long to start (timing issue)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Network connectivity issues within the container&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="check-container-health-status"&gt;Check Container Health Status&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;docker inspect --format&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;{{.State.Health.Status}}&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; &amp;lt;container&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="view-health-check-logs"&gt;View Health Check Logs&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;docker inspect --format&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;{{json .State.Health}}&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; &amp;lt;container&amp;gt; | jq
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="test-health-check-command-manually"&gt;Test Health Check Command Manually&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;docker exec &amp;lt;container&amp;gt; &amp;lt;health-check-command&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="increase-timeout-and-retries"&gt;Increase Timeout and Retries&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-dockerfile" data-lang="dockerfile"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;HEALTHCHECK&lt;/span&gt; --interval&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;30s --timeout&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;10s --start-period&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;60s --retries&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; CMD curl -f http://localhost/ &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;||&lt;/span&gt; exit &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="disable-health-check-temporarily"&gt;Disable Health Check Temporarily&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;docker run --no-healthcheck &amp;lt;image&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="check-application-logs"&gt;Check Application Logs&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;docker logs &amp;lt;container&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Example 1: Health check failing&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;docker ps
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# CONTAINER STATUS: unhealthy&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Fix: check if application is running inside container&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Example 2: Health check timing out&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;docker inspect --format&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;{{json .State.Health}}&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; my-container
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# &amp;#34;Log&amp;#34;: [{&amp;#34;Output&amp;#34;:&amp;#34;curl: (28) Operation timed out&amp;#34;}]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Fix: increase --start-period or check application startup&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Example 3: Wrong health check path&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;HEALTHCHECK CMD curl -f http://localhost:3000/health &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;||&lt;/span&gt; exit &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Fix: verify correct port and path&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/docker/container-exited/"&gt;Container Exited&lt;/a&gt; — container stopped unexpectedly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/kubernetes/pod-crash/"&gt;CrashLoopBackOff&lt;/a&gt; — pod keeps crashing in Kubernetes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>Azure AKS: Container Health Checks Failed</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/cloud/azure/aks-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/cloud/azure/aks-error/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;The AKS container health check failure occurs when Kubernetes liveness or readiness probes fail, causing pods to be restarted or removed from service endpoints. This is the most common cause of application unavailability on AKS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Liveness probe fails because the application is deadlocked or crashed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Readiness probe fails because the application is not ready to serve traffic&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Probe endpoint returns non-200 status code&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Application takes longer to start than the probe&amp;rsquo;s &lt;code&gt;initialDelaySeconds&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Resource limits cause the container to be OOMKilled&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Check pod status and events:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>